Experts Guide for the Media
Journalists can draw on the extensive resource of the UIC faculty. This is a searchable database of hundreds of UIC faculty experts who are often available to help with your stories. You may contact them directly or through the Office of Public Affairs.



Featured Experts



Mark Dworkin
Infectious disease expert Mark Dworkin, a former state epidemiologist, has field experience in outbreak investigations and is author of two books about disease outbreaks in the U.S. and abroad.
View More > 





Zizi Papacharissi
Zizi Papacharissi studies the social and political consequences of new media, and how it sets parameters for political and civic engagement.
View More > 





Stevan Weine
Stevan Weine studies the psychosocial dimensions of trauma, disasters, violent extremism, international and domestic terrorism, and migration.
View More > 





